243
00:11:38,149 --> 00:11:41,610
to not, what I call, overproduce certain objects

244
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:42,330
and environments.

245
00:11:42,871 --> 00:11:45,291
Oftentimes, I would go back and actually take pixels out

246
00:11:46,412 --> 00:11:49,993
and take details out of a sprite or a scene that I had created.

247
00:11:50,713 --> 00:11:53,674
And I really had to just trust the charming, nostalgic appeal

248
00:11:54,135 --> 00:11:56,815
of these old, chunky pixels and simply walk away

249
00:11:56,835 --> 00:11:59,056
from working on a sprite once it was there,

